*Welcome to the So Pekocko API*.

To create the application proceed as follows!

*1: Frontend *

To start, clone the following repo into a folder.
https://github.com/OpenClassrooms-Student-Center/dwj-projet6

To make the project work, you need to install :
- [NodeJS](https://nodejs.org/en/download/) in version 12.14 or 14.0Â 
- Angular CLI](https://github.com/angular/angular-cli) in version 7.0.2.
- [node-sass](https://www.npmjs.com/package/node-sass) : be careful to take the version corresponding to NodeJS. For Node 14.0 for example, install node-sass in version 4.14+.

On Windows, these installations require using PowerShell as administrator.

## Development server

Start ng serve to access the development server. Go to http://localhost:4200/. The application will reload automatically if you modify a source file.


*2: Backend *

To start, copie the backend case into your project's root folder.

Next, in a powershell from the root file, to input the following command

"npm install"

And to start the server, to input 

"npm run start" 

** You can now navigate the application and perform the various operations for this application.
